==Estonian==

===Noun===
'''saal'''

====Pronunciation====
''aa'' is superlong (second quantity). Orthoepy requires a palatalized ''l'' though usually it is not palatalized. 

====Etymology====
From German '''Saal'''.

====Morphology====
Genitive singular: ''saali'' (second quantity).
Partitive singular: ''saali'' (third quantity).
Illative singular: ''saali'' (third quantity) or ''saalisse'' (second quantity). 
Genitive plural: ''saalide'' (third quality).
Partitive plural: ''saale'' (third quality) or ''saalisid'' (third quality).
Illative plural: ''saalidesse'' (third quality).

====Meaning====  
# [[hall]] or large [[room]].
#: ''Saal on täna kinni.'' The hall is closed today.

